.TH maint-buggy 6 "Jan 1 1999" "@MBNAME@ @MBVERS@"
.SH NAME
maint-buggy \- maintain the moon-buggy installation
.SH SYNOPSIS
maint-buggy [--help] [--uninstall] [--version]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B maint-buggy
script is part of the
.B moon-buggy
package.  It helps to maintain your moon-buggy installation and
is only useful for the system administrator.
.SH OPTIONS
The script understands the following options.
.TP
.B --help
shows a short usage message.
.TP
.B --uninstall
removes the
.B moon-buggy
installation from the system.  As this includes the
.B maint-buggy
script itself, this step cannot easily be undone.  Use with
caution!
.IP
Note: If you installed
.B moon-buggy
with the help of a package manager (like rpm) you probably
should use the same program for deinstallation.
.TP
.B --version
prints moon-buggy's version string to standard output and exits.
